                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350511-name-1248" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-1248" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-1248" type="surname" value="CARR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-1248" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN CARR</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a carpenter, and live in York-road, Lambeth. I was at Greenwich fair on the 20th of April, and lost a handkerchief, which I have recovered—it is worth 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—this is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350511-name-1249" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-1249" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-1249" type="surname" value="HOBBS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-1249" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS HOBBS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable C</hi> 85.) I was on duty at Greenwich fair, and saw the prisoner go behind the prosecutor, and take this hand<lb></lb>kerchief out of his pocket—I seized him instantly with it in his hand—he got it quite out of the pocket.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I picked it off the ground—the policeman called out, "Has any gentleman lost a handkerchief?"—the gentleman turned round, and said, he had—he could not exactly swear it was his at first.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
